div.p: An hipothetical e-commerce, deployed on a Kubernetes cluster of 3 nodes from a local machine - localhost - via kubectl. Each node runs a pod based on two containers: a front-end application (i.e. Next.js), which accepts incoming connections from the users and a backend (i.e. Express). The latter serve a REST API between providing data stored on a DB volume managed by a MongoDB service.
